<p>The use of virtual base classes can introduce a number of undefined and potentially confusing behaviours. The use of virtual bases is not
recommended.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
class B {};
class D: public virtual B {}; // Noncompliant, B is a virtual base
</pre>
<h2>See</h2>
<ul>
  <li> MISRA C++:2008, 10-1-1 - Classes should not be derived from virtual bases. </li>
</ul>